@twiecki I also think that the information analysis doesn't need the group_adjust (now group_neutral) flag. 

Currently and historically that flag is used to perform returns demeaning before computing the IC between factor values and returns. Subtracting a constant (the mean value) to the returns doesn't affect the value of IC (IC is Spearman's rank correlation coefficient), so we should get rid of this flag all around the information analysis API, unless there is a plan to change the way IC is computed (but we can still restore the flag in the future if needed).

Please let me know what you think and in case I'll add a commit in this PR to remove the flag.

